<H1>Changing to another login shell</H1>

<P>To change the shell that you enter whenever you log in
to the system use the <STRONG>chsh</STRONG> (change shell) command.  Next
time you login you will use the new shell.</P>

<P>You must reset any <A HREF="../environment/env5.html">shell</A>
and <A HREF="../environment/index.html">environment</A> variables
that you set in your previous shell's startup file. If
you do not they will no longer be in effect.</P>

